Statements made as to sentencing.  
As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 66 MONTHS, concurrent with 12CF6211, with credit for 79 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 30 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 36 MONTHS.  

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant is appropriate for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees, and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Conditions of extended supervision:
1) No illegal drugs;
2) AODA Assessment and comply with treatment or counseling deemed appropriate;
3) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay by end of extended supervision will result in a civil judgment; 
4) Successfully complete an anger management/a Batterers Intervention program;
5) Mental health evaluation and take all prescribed medication; Attend parenting class; 
6) AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
7) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
8) No contact with any place drugs are sold, packaged or used;
9) No controlled substances without prescription; If defendant has a prescription he is to report it to his agent;
10) Obtain GED/HSED and participate in vocational training and cognitive thinking class;

Exhibit 1 received into evidence by the Court. Exhibit list received and filed. Court recommends the DVD received into evidence be sent to the institution so the supervisors know what kind of gun is involved.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting 

